        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(infra): bound jsonl-socket response buffer to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`requestJsonlSocket` accumulates incoming socket data into a string buffer until a newline is seen or the socket closes. A buggy or hostile peer that streams data without newlines can force the runtime to keep buffering until timeout or OOM.\n\nThis PR bounds that pending JSONL line buffer in the shared requester. It intentionally does not change producer output contracts. The cap is set to 16 MiB so the requester still has a finite memory bound while reducing compatibility risk for large but valid shared JSONL responses such as exec-host command output.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts`\n  - Adds `JSONL_SOCKET_MAX_BUFFER_BYTES = 16 * 1024 * 1024`.\n  - Returns `null` and destroys the socket once the pending line buffer exceeds the cap.\n  - Exposes the cap through `testApi` so tests stay aligned with the production limit.\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts`\n  - Adds a regression test for an oversized newline-free socket response.\n  - Streams chunks over the real socket until the production cap is exceeded and handles the expected server-side EPIPE after the requester destroys the socket.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: A peer streaming a newline-free body larger than the cap must not hang or grow memory until timeout; the call must return `null` quickly.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Node v22 workspace, real `net.createServer` / `net.Socket` over a Unix domain socket in `/tmp`.\n- **Exact steps**: `node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts` starts a server that streams 64 KiB chunks every 5 ms with no newline, then calls `requestJsonlSocket` with a 2 s timeout.\n- **Observed result after fix**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104`.\n- **Negative control on current main**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016`.\n\n## Scope correction proof\n\n- **Current head**: `fc09c0d048c1188ac954098a875cb52f9f7029a3`.\n- **Current GitHub PR diff**: `+49/-1 (2 files)`.\n- **Current changed files**:\n\n```text\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\nThe previous macOS exec-host producer changes were removed from the final PR diff. This PR now only changes the shared JSONL requester and its focused regression test.\n\n## Compatibility note\n\nThe previous 1 MiB cap was too tight for a shared JSONL requester because `requestJsonlSocket` is also used by the exec-host path. This revision raises the cap to 16 MiB to keep the OOM guard bounded while leaving substantially more room for valid command output responses.\n\nThis still does not define a producer-side exec-host output contract. If maintainers want exact stdout/stderr truncation semantics, that should remain a separate owner-reviewed PR.\n\n## Evidence\n\nTerminal proof (real socket, streaming peer without newlines):\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104\n```\n\nNegative control (temporary revert to `origin/main`):\n\n```text\n$ git checkout origin/main -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016\n$ git checkout HEAD -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\nFocused Vitest after raising the cap to 16 MiB:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts --run\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  6 passed (6)\n```\n\nWhitespace/check sanity after raising the cap to 16 MiB:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n# exit 0\n```\n\nEarlier type checks on this PR:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm tsgo:core      # exit 0\n$ pnpm tsgo:core:test # exit 0\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix/jsonl-socket-buffer-bound",
